{{multiple| {{primary|date=June 2017}} {{sources|date=June 2017}} }} {{Infobox sport governing body | name = Albanian Mixed Martial Arts Federation | native name = Federata Shqiptare e Ndeshjes së Lirë | abbrev = AMMAF | logo = Federata Shqiptare e Ndeshjes së Lirë.svg | logosize = 200px | sport = [[Mixed martial arts|MMA]] | category = | image = | caption = | jurisdiction = [[Albania]] | founded = 2012 | aff = [[International Mixed Martial Arts Federation|IMMAF]] | affdate = |region = |regionyear = | headquarters = [[Tirana]] | location = | president = Arjan Rizaj | vicepresident = | secretary = | coach = | womenscoach = | key staff = | operating income = | sponsor = | year closed = | replaced = | prevfounded = | url = https://www.ammaf.org/ | countryflag = }} The '''Albanian Mixed Martial Arts Federation''' ('''AMMAF''' or '''FSHNJ''') ({{lang-sq|Federata Shqiptare e Ndeshjes së Lirë}}) is the head [[Sport governing body|governing body]] for the sport of professional [[Mixed martial arts|MMA]] and promotion of this sport in [[Albania]].
The ''AMMAF'' was founded in 2012 by Arjan Rizaj (currently President of the AMMAF) to improve and promote the [[Mixed martial arts|MMA]] in the country, such as [[boxing]]; [[wrestling]]; [[kickboxing]]; [[Brazilian Jiu Jitsu]] and others [[martial arts]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ammaf.org/rreth-nesh|title=AMMAF - Albanian Mixed Martial Arts Federation}}</ref> The Federation is also recognized by the [[Ministry of Education and Sport (Albania)|Ministry of Education and Sport]] and is a member of the [[International Mixed Martial Arts Federation]] (IMMAF).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.immaf.org/members/|title=Members - IMMAF|publisher=}}</ref>
==History==
{{Incomplete section|date=June 2017}} The Albanian Mixed Martial Arts Federation was founded in 2012 and is a full-fledged member of the [[International Mixed Martial Arts Federation]] ''(IMMAF)''.
