"'''As-Salam al-Malaki'''" ({{Lang-ar|السلام الملكي}}, literally "The Royal Salute") was the national anthem of the [[Kingdom of Iraq]] from 1932 to 1958.
==History==
{{National anthems of Iraq}}
It was composed by Iraqi Army Band director Lieutenant A. Chaffon in 1924, a British military officer.<ref>http://www.nationalanthems.info/iq-58.htm</ref>
==See also==
{{Portal|Iraq}}
*"[[Ardulfurataini (national anthem)|Ardulfurataini]]", the former Iraqi national anthem, used from 1981 to 2003.
*"[[Mawtini]]", the current Iraqi national anthem since 2003.

