{{Infobox journal | title = Musicae Scientiae | cover = Musicae Scientiae.jpg | editor = Reinhard Kopiez | discipline = [[Music psychology]] | former_names = | abbreviation = Music. Sci. | publisher = [[Sage Publications]] on behalf of the [[European Society for the Cognitive Sciences of Music]] | country = | frequency = Quarterly | history = 1992-present | openaccess = | license = | impact = 1.537 | impact-year = 2013 | website = http://www.sagepub.com/journals/Journal202036/title | link1 = http://msx.sagepub.com/content/current | link1-name = Online access | link2 = http://msx.sagepub.com/content/by/year | link2-name = Online archive | JSTOR = | OCLC = 463081059 | LCCN = sn98052141 | CODEN = | ISSN = 1029-8649 | eISSN = 2045-4147 }} '''''Musicae Scientiae''''' is a quarterly [[peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] covering the field of [[music psychology]]. The [[editor-in-chief]] is Reinhard Kopiez ([[Hochschule für Musik, Theater und Medien Hannover]]). It was established 1997 and is published by [[Sage Publications]] on behalf of the [[European Society for the Cognitive Sciences of Music]].
== Abstracting and indexing == The journal is abstracted and indexed in the [[Arts & Humanities Citation Index]], [[Current Contents]]/Arts & Humanities, Current Contents/Social & Behavioral Sciences, and the [[Social Sciences Citation Index]]. According to the ''[[Journal Citation Reports]]'', the journal has a 2013 [[impact factor]] of 1.537<ref name=WoS>{{cite book |year=2014 |chapter=Journals Ranked by Impact: Psychology, Experimental |title=2013 [[Journal Citation Reports]] |publisher=[[Thomson Reuters]] |edition=Social Sciences |work=[[Web of Science]] |postscript=.}}</ref>
