{{Advert|date=August 2010}} {{Infobox company | name = Spellbound Entertainment AG | logo = Spellbound Entertainment.png | type = [[Public company|Public]] | successor = [[Black Forest Games]] | foundation = {{Start date and age|1994}} | defunct = {{End date|2012}} | location_city = [[Offenburg]] | location_country = [[Germany]] | industry = [[Video game industry]] | num_employees = 40 | num_employees_year = 2011 }}
'''Spellbound Entertainment AG''' was German [[video game developer]] based in [[Offenburg]]. Founded in 1994 by [[Armin Gessert]], the company is best known for the ''Desperados'' series.
They also developed ''[[Arcania: Gothic 4]]'', part of the [[Gothic (Series)|''Gothic'' series]] and later its expansion, ''[[Arcania: Fall of Setarrif]]''. It was Spellbound's first entry into the series, which was previously developed by [[Piranha Bytes]].
== Company == Spellbound was founded in 1994.
In 2007, they developed ''[[Arcania: Gothic 4]]'', the new chapter in the [[Gothic (series)|''Gothic'' series]].
In 2012 the company went into administration.<ref>http://www.gameswelt.ch/news/157432-Spellbound_Entertainment_AG_-_Deutscher_Entwickler_meldet_Insolvenz_an.html</ref> They were re-founded as [[Black Forest Games]] <ref>http://www.gamestar.de/news/branche/2569952/spellbound.html</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.black-forest-games.com/company/studio.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2015-06-12 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121211044843/http://black-forest-games.com/company/studio.html |archivedate=2012-12-11 |df= }}</ref>
